  "@type": "Article",
  "dateModified": "2026-03-06",
  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "Exposition is the delivery of information the reader needs to understand the story — backstory, world rules, character history, context. It is the writer\u0026rsquo;s answer to the question \u0026ldquo;what does the reader need to know, and when do they need to know it?\u0026rdquo;\nExposition is necessary and often unavoidable. The reader of a fantasy novel needs to understand the magic system. The reader of a crime novel needs to understand the victim\u0026rsquo;s relationships. The reader of a literary novel needs to understand a character\u0026rsquo;s past. The craft problem is not whether to include exposition but how to deliver it without stopping the story.\n",
